!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

uniform /ˈjuːnɪˌfɔːm/

(uniforms) 

1. N-VAR A uniform is a special set of clothes which some people, for example soldiers or the police, wear to work in and which some children wear in school. 制服 

例： The police wear dark blue uniforms. 警察穿深蓝色制服。 

例： Felipe was in uniform for the parade. 费利佩穿着游行服装。 

2. ADJ If something is uniform , it does not vary, but is even and regular throughout. 一致的 

例： Cut down between the bones so that all the chops are of uniform size. 在骨头之间砍削，使所有的排骨大小一致。 

例： All flowing water, though it appears to be uniform, is actually divided into extensive inner surfaces, or layers, moving against one another. 所有流水尽管看起来是一样的，实际上是分成了大量相互碰撞的内在表层。 

3. uniformity N-UNCOUNT 一致性 

例： ...the caramel that was used to maintain uniformity of colour in the brandy. …为保持白兰地色泽一致而添加的焦糖。 

4. ADJ If you describe a number of things as uniform , you mean that they are all the same. 同样的 

例： Along each wall stretched uniform green metal filing cabinets. 沿每堵墙摆放着清一色的绿色金属档案柜。 

5. uniformity N-UNCOUNT 相同性 

例： ...the dull uniformity of the houses. …那些房子的单调雷同。

